cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "CoordPy: Coordinating LLM agent teams with content-addressed context"
message: "If you use CoordPy in research, please cite it using this metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "CoordPy Contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/adotdong29/CoordPy"
url: "https://github.com/adotdong29/CoordPy"
abstract: >
  coordpy models cross-agent context as typed, content-addressed
  objects with byte budgets, declared parents, and a fixed
  lifecycle. A run produces a RunReport whose root is a sealed
  capsule DAG, plus a provenance manifest, that downstream tools
  can re-verify from the bytes on disk.
keywords:
  - multi-agent
  - llm
  - context
  - provenance
  - evaluation
license: MIT
